I would suggest that you make ashton mail interchange a terminus
and run trains from there to rencross
the reason being the way simutrans routes
i knew you'd have a reason!
always :) It first looks for the least # of transfers
and if two routes have the same number of transfers, it goes for whichever has the shortest first leg
but not neccesarily the shortest full trip
ah, the greedy algorithm
So the way it is currently set up, all traffic going from oldham, malichester, and renham to points north goes out by way of rencross
But all reverse traffic comes in through oakstead
this=major traffic imbalance
so by placing a mandatory transfer at ashton, train loads will be more balanced and, in general, full
